title: Cages
summaries: Cages are placeable decorative furniture items that display animated critters. A critter caught with the Bug Net, Lavaproof Bug Net(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions), or Golden Bug Net(Desktop, Console and Mobile versions) is combined with a Terrarium to craft a cage.
Gold cages (Desktop, Console and Mobile versions) are regular cages containing gold critters. They sell for 10 GC each. Aside from the sell price, they are the same as regular cages.

Cages are background furniture, and nothing can be placed on them, nor can they be placed on top of each other. On the <linked>[img:Desktop version]</linked><linked> Desktop version</linked>, <linked>[img:Console version]</linked><linked> Console version</linked>, and <linked>[img:Mobile version]</linked><linked> Mobile version</linked>, cages can be stacked and stood on like platforms.
All cages measure either 6 tiles wide by 3 high, or 3 tiles wide by 2 high, and are partially transparent.

On the <linked>[img:Desktop version]</linked><linked> Desktop version</linked>, <linked>[img:Console version]</linked><linked> Console version</linked>, and <linked>[img:Mobile version]</linked><linked> Mobile version</linked>, cages can be converted back into their ingredients by throwing the cage into <linked>shimmer</linked>.

On the <linked>[img:Old-gen console version]</linked><linked> Old-gen console version</linked> and <linked>Nintendo 3DS</linked><linked>[img:Nintendo 3DS version]</linked><linked> version</linked>, cages cannot be opened, broken, or crafted back into their ingredients, so once a critter is crafted into a cage, that particular critter can no longer be released.
There are currently (Desktop, Console and Mobile versions) 63 / (Old-gen console and 3DS versions) 17 cages, (Desktop, Console and Mobile versions) 10 of which are gold variants.
